## Local .gitignore for NQueen repository
## Machine-wide .NET rules are in: C:\Users\ramin\.gitignore_global
## Register with: git config --global core.excludesfile "$env:USERPROFILE\.gitignore_global"

## ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
## TODO (when copying this file to a new repo as a template):
##
## KEEP AS-IS (fully generic .NET/VS rules — no edits needed):
##   Build output, Visual Studio, StyleCop, Mono, Visual C++ cache,
##   Click-Once/Publish, Microsoft Azure, Windows Store,
##   Visual Studio cache files, SQL Server, Business Intelligence,
##   Upgrade/migration reports, Misc.
##
## ADJUST (opt-in sections — uncomment only if the repo uses them):
##   BenchmarkDotNet  — uncomment if the repo has a benchmarking project.
##   ASP.NET Scaffolding — uncomment if the repo uses ASP.NET scaffolding.
##   Code Coverage    — simplify to just **/TestResults/ and CoverageReport/
##                      unless you want to selectively track specific files.
##
## REMOVE / REPLACE (project-specific entries — must be updated per repo):
##   /NQueen.GUI/NQueen Results.xlsm  — replace with repo-specific output files.
##   The 4 !CoverageReport/badge_*.svg and !CoverageReport/index.html lines
##     — only keep if this repo tracks those exact coverage report files.
##   This header comment — update the repo name.
## ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

